### Authentication & Authorization - Patient Management API

## 1. LOGIN (Get JWT Token)
POST http://localhost:3000/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "admin",
  "password": "admin123"
}

###

## 2. LOGIN as Staff Member
POST http://localhost:3000/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "staff1",
  "password": "staff123"
}

###

## 3. GET All Patients (Requires Authentication)
# Use token from login response
GET http://localhost:3000/patients
Authorization: Bearer eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9...

###

## 4. GET Patient by ID
GET http://localhost:3000/patients/1
Authorization: Bearer eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9...

###

## 5. POST - Add New Patient (Admin Only)
POST http://localhost:3000/patients
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9...

{
  "patient_name": "Sandeep Kumar",
  "age": 40,
  "gender": "M",
  "contact_number": "9876543218",
  "email": "sandeep.kumar@email.com",
  "admission_date": "2025-01-10",
  "medical_condition": "Kidney Issue",
  "room_number": "109",
  "bed_number": "D",
  "status": "Active"
}

###

## 6. PUT - Update Patient (Admin Only)
PUT http://localhost:3000/patients/1
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9...

{
  "patient_name": "Rajesh Kumar Singh",
  "medical_condition": "Cardiac Issue - Stable",
  "status": "Stable"
}

###

## 7. DELETE Patient (Admin Only)
DELETE http://localhost:3000/patients/8
Authorization: Bearer eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9...

###

## NOTES:
## - Admin credentials: username: admin, password: admin123
## - Staff credentials: username: staff1, password: staff123
## - GET, PUT, DELETE require admin role
## - GET requires authentication (admin or staff can view)
## - POST, PUT, DELETE can only be done by admin
## - All requests require valid JWT token in Authorization header
